– First encryption update About Blog Help Jobs First encryption update Laying the privacy foundation Michael Donohue Jul 8, Our vision at HalloApp is to build a simple, safe, private place to connect, share and communicate about what matters in your life, with the people who matter in your Your real relationships in complete Weâve known from the beginning that to deliver on that promise long term, it canât just be the whim of todayâs team to keep that data secure - we need strong technical measures to keep it secure into the future, and as our team The best way to do that is to keep the data inaccessible to anyone, including ourselves, who isnât a party to the This completely mitigates the problems of cybercriminals, hackers, rogue employees, data leaks, or psychological studies done without your We canât lose control of data we donât have to begin So today we are introducing encrypted chats, based on the well known Signal By starting with “Chats”, we are establishing secure channels between individual users, and we will use that as a building block to encrypt all traffic on our network We are announcing this today as a key milestone toward encrypting group posts and home You can validate your encryption keys with another HalloApp user by opening their profile screen, and selecting ‘verify safety number’ from the overflow We are looking to build a team that focuses on encryption and would love to speak with you if you are interested in the area and want to work on building a world class product with world class encryption at the heart of About Blog Help Jobs Terms Privacy Â© HalloApp   HalloApp – Help About Blog Help Jobs Help You can find a list of frequently asked questions If you have any other questions, comments, or feedback we would love to hear from FAQ What is HalloApp? HalloApp is the first app for real A simple, safe, and private place to connect and share what matters in your life, with the people who matter to In complete Do you have an Android and iPhone app? Yes, HalloApp is currently and we have both an Android and iPhone We provide support for: Android (lollipop) and above, iPhone iOS and above (iphone or higher) Can I use HalloApp worldwide or just in the United States? HalloApp can be used How do I install HalloApp? Go to download or search for HalloApp in the Android play store or Apple app store directly to install the You can also get an invitation by an existing HalloApp user and follow the link that they have sent you from your phone to install I installed HalloApp, what s next? Use your phone number to register and start using HalloApp needs access to your contacts on your phone to connect you to your We only send phone numbers to our server to match with friends - no other contact info leaves your How do I update HalloApp? We’re continually improving To make sure your app is turn on the automatic updates on your phone or visit your app store to manually How do I connect with my friends & family? HalloApp uses your phone’s contact book to connect you with your friends & You can use the privacy settings in the app to restrict which of your contacts have access to your Does HalloApp use my wifi or cellular data? Yes, HalloApp uses the same internet connection as web browsing and email on your Will data roaming charges apply if I use HalloApp when I am traveling? Yes, data roaming charges may To avoid any roaming charges turn off your mobile data Contact your mobile provider for more Can I use the same HalloApp account on multiple phone numbers? Your HalloApp account can be associated with only one phone number at a Can I change my phone number on HalloApp? How? Yes, you’ll need to delete your HalloApp account and you’ll be presented with a registration screen to register with your new phone Please note that your data will be deleted from your previous account associated with your old phone Who can see my posts? Your post will be shared with your phone contacts who also use You can limit your contact book’s access to your posts by using the privacy settings in the I see some comments on the posts of my friends from people who are not in my address Who are they and can they see my phone number? The people who are not in your address book can only see a name and no other The comments that you see on your friends posts are from your friends’ You will not be able to see each other’s phone numbers unless you are mutual Do my posts expire? Your posts will no longer be visible to your contacts after In order to be able to forward incoming replies during those days, posts are temporarily stored on our servers, but are then completely deleted from our servers after Do my messages expire? No, messages don’t We temporarily store messages on our servers until they are delivered to the The double check indicates device delivery, and that we no longer have the message on our Once they are delivered, they stay on your phone until you decide to delete Also - all messages are encrypted, so
